{{Infobox Hindu temple | name = Bhutandevi Temple | image = | image_alt = | caption = A view of Bhutandevi Temple | proper_name = Bhutandevi Temple भुटनदेवी मन्दिर
| country = [[Nepal]] | state = | district = [[Makwanpur District]] | locale = [[Hetauda]] | elevation_m = | deity = Goddess Bhutandevi | festivals= Dashain | architecture = [[Pagoda]] | temple_quantity = 1 | monument_quantity= 1 | inscriptions = | date_built = | creator = | website = }} {{Hinduism small}}
'''Bhutandevi Mandir''' ({{lang-ne|भुटनदेवी मन्दिर}}) is a [[Hindu temple]] dedicated to Goddess [[Hidimbi|Bhutandevi]] (a.k.a. [[Hidimbi]]), said to be the [[wife]] of [[Bhim]] (One of the [[Pandavas]]) and [[mother]] of [[Ghatotkacha]]. [[Hidimbi|Butandevi]] is actually another form of goddess [[Durga]]. Situated at Butandevi Road-10 in [[Hetauda]], a town in [[Makwanpur district]] of [[Nepal]],. It is about 15 minute walkable distance from Hetauda Bus Park.the temple of Butandevi i.e. The temple was designed according to [[Vastu Shastra|Vastu principles]] and it is believed that worshipping the goddess helps one to get victory over serious troubles, problems and fear.<ref>http://allhindutemples.com/city/makawanpur/hindu_temple/bhutandevi-temple/</ref>
