{{Jainism}}
'''Acharya Guptinandi Ji'''<ref>{{citation |url=http://jainmunilocator.org/munis.php?id=194|title=ACHARYA SHRI 108 GUPTINANDI JI MAHARAJ|work=jainmunilocator.org }}</ref> is a ''[[Digambara monk]]'' initiated by ''[[Acharya (Jainism)|Acharya]]'' Kunthusagar.

==Biography==
''[[Acharya (Jainism)|Acharya]]'' Guptinandi was born in the city of [[Bhopal]], [[Madhya Pradesh]] on 1 August 1972.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://jinaagamsaar.com/aacharya/guptinandi.php|title=Aacharya Shri 108 Guptinandi Ji Maharaj|work=jinaagamsaar.com }}</ref> He did his [[B.Com]] as a ''[[Sravaka (Jainism)|Sravaka]]'' (lay follower) and was initiated as a ''[[Digambara monk]]'' on 22 July 1991 by ''Acharya'' Kunthusagar.{{sfn|Flügel|2006|p=352}} In December 2014, he went to [[Jaipur]], [[Rajasthan]], where he gave the title of ''Yuva Munishi'' to Muni Suyashgupt and ''Jin Dharma Prabhavak'' to Muni Chandragupta.<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.bhaskar.com/news/RAJ-JAI-city-of-saints-union-acharya-guptinandi-4825033-PHO.html|title=24 साल बाद आए आचार्य बोले- पिंकसिटी संतों के मिलन की सिटी|work=bhaskar.com }}</ref> He got the ''Acharya Pad'' on 27 May 2001 in [[Indore]], [[Madhya Pradesh]].

He is the founder of Shri Dharm Tirth. He supervised the ''[[Panchkalyanak]]'' at Manasinganahalli, held in 2013.<ref>{{citation |title=Panchakalyana Mahotsava at Manasinganahalli|url=http://www.jainheritagecentres.com/index.php/news/news-updates/1282-panchakalyana-mahotsava-at-manasinganahalli|work=jainheritagecentres.com}}</ref>

==Chaturmas==
*2014 - Bholanath Nagar, [[Delhi]]<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.herenow4u.net/index.php?id=99670|title=CHATURMAS VENUES OF JAIN SAINTS FOR THE YEAR 2014 (DIGAMBAR SECT)|work=herenow4u.net}}</ref>
*2011 - Badout, [[Meerut]], [[Uttar Pradesh]]<ref>{{citation |url=http://jainsquare.com/author/jainsquare/page/501|title=Chaturmas List Of 2011|work=jainsquare.com }}</ref>
*2009 - [[Sonagiri]], [[Madhya Pradesh]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digambarjainonline.com/news/news17b.htm|title=CHATURMAS Digambar Saints and Sadhvi - 2009|work=digambarjainonline.com}}</ref>

