{{infobox WorldScouting | type = | name = International Link of Orthodox Christian Scouts | image = International Link of Orthodox Christian Scouts.svg | image-size = | caption = | headquarters = | location = | country = International | f-date = | founder = | award-for = | members = | chiefscouttitle = Secretary General | chiefscout = | chiefscouttitle2 = | chiefscout2 = | owner = | website =http://www.desmos.info/ }}
The '''International Link of Orthodox Christian Scouts''' (DESMOS, from [[Greek language|Greek]] "Δεσμός", bond) is an autonomous, international body committed to promoting and supporting Orthodox Scout associations and to be a link between the Scout movement and [[Eastern Orthodox Church|Orthodox churches]].
It enjoys consultative status with the World Scout Committee and forms the World Scout Inter-religious Forum (WSIF)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wsis2009.org/scouting_wsif.php |title=World Scout Inter-religious Forum (WSIF) |accessdate=2010-01-08 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090413023825/http://wsis2009.org/scouting_wsif.php |archivedate=April 13, 2009 }}</ref> together with the [[Council of Protestants in Guiding and Scouting]], [[International Catholic Conference of Scouting]], [[International Union of Muslim Scouts]], International Forum of Jewish Scouts, Won-Buddhism Scout and [[World Buddhist Scout Brotherhood]].
==Member organizations== * Egypt: Boys and Girls scouts started 1914 but physically worked by 2012 [[all over Egypt]] * Kuwait: Boys scouts started 2003- whereas Girl's scouts started at 2018- [[all over Kuwait]] * Armenia: [[Hayastani Azgayin Skautakan Sharjum Kazmakerputiun]]<ref name="DESMOS statutes">{{cite web |url=http://www.desmos.info/en/statutes.html |title=DEMOS statutes |accessdate=2010-08-18}}</ref> * Bosnia and Herzegovina: [[Savez izviđača Bosne i Hercegovine]] (supports by [[Roman Catholics]] and [[Islam]]) * Bulgaria: [[Organizatsia na Bulgarskite Skauty]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.desmos.info/en/doc/DesmosDocuments/Desmos_Committee_Meeting_Sofia_2005_Minutes.pdf |title=DESMOS committee meeting |accessdate=2010-08-18}}</ref> * Cyprus: [[Cyprus Scouts Association]]<ref name="DESMOS statutes"/> * Finland: [[Suomen Partiolaiset]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.desmos.info/en/doc/DesmosDocuments/4th_Desmos_Conference_Tunisia_2005_Summary.pdf |title=4th DESMOS conference |accessdate=2010-08-18}}</ref> * Greece: [[Scouts of Greece]]<ref name="DESMOS statutes"/> * Israel: [[Israel Boy and Girl Scouts Federation]]: Christian Orthodox Scout Association * Jordan: [[Jordanian Association for Boy Scouts and Girl Guides]]: Jordanian Association for Boy Scouts and Girl Guides * Lebanon: [[Lebanese Scouting Federation]]: National Orthodox Scout Association - Scout national orthodoxe<ref name="DESMOS statutes"/> * Macedonia: [[Sojuz na Izvidnici na Makedonija]] * Moldova: [[Organizaţia Naţională a Scouţilor din Moldova]] * Palestinian Authority: [[Palestinian Scout Association]]: Palestinian Orthodox Scouts Association<ref name="DESMOS statutes"/> * Poland: [[Polish Scouting and Guiding Association]]<ref name="DESMOS statutes"/> * Romania: [[Cercetaşii României]]<ref name="DESMOS statutes"/> * Russia: [[Russian Association of Scouts/Navigators]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.desmos.info/en/doc/RUSSIA_joins_DESMOS%20_for_web_site-News_Info_.pdf |title=Russian federation joins DESMOS |accessdate=2010-08-18}}</ref> * Serbia: [[Savez Izviđača Srbije]]<ref name="DESMOS statutes"/> * Uganda: [[The Uganda Scouts Association]]: Uganda Orthodox Scouts<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.desmos.info/en/news.html |title=Uganda - new DESMOS member-country |accessdate=2010-08-18}}</ref> * Ukraine: [[National Organization of Scouts of Ukraine]] * United States: [[Boy Scouts of America]]: Eastern Orthodox Committee on Scouting<ref name="DESMOS statutes"/>
